article.headline: Kennesaw 88, Jacksonville 64
article.story: KENNESAW, Ga. (AP) -- Golden Ingle scored 18 points, including four 3-pointers, to lead Kennesaw State to an 88-64 Atlantic Sun Conference victory over Jacksonville Monday night. Ingle, the conference player of the week after leading the Owls to three straight wins last week, led five Kennesaw players in double figures as the Owls (9-8, 7-1 ASun) handed the Dolphins their 12th straight loss. Jacksonville (1-14, 1-7) got a career-high 17 points from Mario Brown, who hit 8-of-11 from the floor and pulled down a team-high five rebounds. The Owls hit 11 from 3-point range, including nine in the first half as they went out to a 27-9 lead seven minutes into the game. The Dolphins never recovered and trailed 54-27 at the half. Andre Morgan and Ronell Wooten scored 14 points each for Kennesaw, which also got 11 apiece from Brent Ragsdale and Israel Ingle.
